[block level element]
-> always starts on a new line
-> can have customized margin and padding
-> can contain other block level as well as inline level elements
-> takes up the entire width of its parent element by default
-> height is adjusted to fit the content and other elements it contains by default
-> address,aside,canvas,div,dt,figcaption,footer,h1-h6,hr,main,noscript,p,section,tfoot,video,article,blockquote,dd,dl,
fieldset,figure,form,header,li,nav,ol,pre,table,ul

[inline level element]
-> Doesn't require a new line to start
-> top and bottom margin cannot be adjusted unless the display type is changed via css
-> can only contain data or other inline level elements
-> a,acronym,bdo,br,cite,dfn,i,input,label,object,q,script,small,strong,sup,time,var,abbr,b,big,button,code,em,img,kbd,
map,output,samp,select,span,sub,textarea,tt

[meta tags]
<meta http-equiv="" content="" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
